    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-04-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-04-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="345"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d345">
                <head>345. Minutes of the 10th Meeting of the National Security Council<note n="0"
                        type="source" xml:id="d345fn0">Source: <persName corresp="#p_THS1"
                            >Truman</persName> Library, Papers of <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Harry
                            S. Truman</persName>, President’s Secretary’s Files, Subject File. Top
                        Secret. The meeting was held in the Conference Room at the White House.
                        Although the series of Presidential memoranda on the <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                            >NSC</gloss> meetings begins with the 9th meeting, no such memorandum
                        was found for the 10th session.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-04-22"
                        >April 22, 1948</date>.</dateline>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPANTS</head>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Members Present</hi>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FJV1">James V. Forrestal</persName>, Secretary of
                        Defense, Presiding</item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LRA1">Robert A. Lovett</persName>, Under Secretary of
                        State</item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RKC1">Kenneth C. Royall</persName>, Secretary of the
                        Army</item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SJL1">John L. Sullivan</persName>, Secretary of the
                        Navy</item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWS1">W. Stuart Symington</persName>, Secretary of the
                        Air Force</item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HAM1">Arthur M. Hill</persName>, Chairman, National
                        Security Resources Board </item>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Others Present</hi>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HRAR1">Rear Admiral R. H. Hillenkoetter</persName>,
                        Director of Central Intelligence</item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WCV1">C. V. Whitney</persName>, Assistant Secretary of
                        the Air Force </item>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretariat</hi>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SRASW1">Sidney W. Souers</persName>, Executive
                        Secretary</item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LJSJ1">James S. Lay, Jr.</persName>, Assistant
                        Executive Secretary</item>
                </list>
                <p rend="center">DECISIONS</p>
                <p>[Here follows a decision on the U.S. position with respect to support for Western
                    Union and other related free countries.]</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">2. Protection of Intelligence Sources and Methods From
                        Unauthorized Disclosures</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d345fn1">Paragraphs a–b constitute <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                            >NSC</gloss> Action No. 45. (National Archives and Records
                        Administration, RG 273, Records of the National Security Council, Record of
                        Actions, Box 55)</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>a.</label>
                    <item>Agreed that a National Security Council Directive should be issued on this
                        subject.</item>
                    <label>b.</label>
                    <item>Directed the Executive Secretary to prepare such a Directive and submit it
                        for approval by the Council.<note n="2" xml:id="d345fn2">The directive was
                            not issued until January 1950 when the Council approved <gloss
                                target="#t_NSCID1">NSCID</gloss> Nos. 11 and 12 (<ref target="#d430"
                                >Documents 430</ref> and <ref target="#d431">431</ref>).</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>[Here follows a decision on review of the world situation as it relates to the
                    security of the United States.]</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
